This paper is primarily focused on privacy and security issues related to websites, which suggests that it would likely fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of automated website scanning and data protection authorities, which could also relate to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also mentions the potential for website owners to improve their sites based on the transparency resulting from published assessments, which could relate to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
